item.title: Need commands help!
item.dc:creator: @Kidpaparoach Kidpaparoach
item.description:
@Kidpaparoach wrote:

This would be pretty difficult. Rather than actually creating another player/npc you’d be best of just getting the server to draw a copy of the player at that time and declare it as a solid object etc then from their you could make it into an npc with some generic (most probably complicated) code by like putting the drawn player onto an npc model so that the created npc could have characteristics other npcs has such as movement.
Adding it into your server would take a lot of time and skill; I don’t think it’s worth it for you to pursue it however it is a pretty cool idea.
